 United States Air Force  Captain Lesniak enlisted in the Air Force in August 1993 as a Supply Technician  and was initially assigned to Griffiss AFB  NY  He was later assigned to the 92nd Supply Squadron  Fairchild AFB  WA  at which time he was selected for two deployments to the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia  In 1999 he re trained into the Special Investigations career field  As a Special Agent  one of his assignments included the position of the OL Chief  AFOSI Detachment 515 OL A  Rhein Main AB  Germany  During this assignment  he deployed in support of Operation Joint Forge to Bosnia and Herzegovina  While subsequently assigned to the AFOSI Region 3  Scott AFB  IL  he was chosen to deploy in support of Operation Iraqi Freedom  as a member of the Joint Strategic Counterintelligence Directorate  Baghdad  Iraq  Captain Lesniak was selected to attend the Air Force Officer Training School  Maxwell AFB  AL in 2007  He was commissioned as a Second Lieutenant in August 2008  and subsequently assigned to HQ AFOSI  Andrews AFB  MD  During this assignment  he was once again selected to deploy in support of Operation Iraqi Freedom  where he served in a joint special operations unit at Balad AB  Iraq  During his following assignment as the Director of Operations at the 11th Field Investigations Squadron  Joint Base San Antonio Lackland  TX  Captain Lesniak was selected to serve at the AFROTC Detachment 880  Virginia Military Institute  Lexington  VA  where he is currently assigned  EDUCATION 2006 Bachelor of Science degree in Criminal Justice Administration  University of Phoenix  Phoenix  AZ ASSIGNMENTS 1  Nov 1993   May 1995  Supply Technician  469th Supply Squadron  Griffiss AFB  NY 2  June 1995   April 1999  Supply Journeyman  92nd Supply Squadron  Fairchild AFB  WA  May 96   July 96  Supply Journeyman  4404th Expeditionary Wing  Riyadh AB  KSA  Jan 98   Mar 98  Supply Journeyman  4408th Expeditionary Wing  Al Kharj AB  KSA  3  April 1999   July 1999  Student  Air Force Special Investigations Academy  Andrews AFB  MD 4  July 1999   Jan 2001  Special Agent  AFOSI Detachment 224  Cannon AFB  NM 5  Jan 2001   Oct 2001  Student  Defense Language Institute  Presidio of Monterey  CA 6  Nov 2001   Nov 2004  Special Agent  AFOSI Detachment 515 OL A  Rhein Main AB  GE  Jan 2003 June 2003  Special Agent In Charge  401st Expeditionary Air Base Group  Tuzla Air Base  Bosnia and Herzegovina  7  Nov 2004   May 2007  Special Agent  AFOSI Region 3  Scott AFB  IL  July 2005   Jan 2006  Team Leader  Joint Strategic Counterintelligence Directorate  Baghdad  IZ  8  June 2007   May 2008  Special Agent  AFOSI Detachment 613  Kunsan AB  ROK 9  May 2008   August 2008  Officer Trainee  Air Force Officer Training School  Maxwell AFB  AL 10  Aug 2008   June 2011  Special Agent  HQ AFOSI  Andrews AFB  MD  July 2009   Jan 2010  Task Force Counterintelligence Coordinating Authority  Joint Special Operations Task Force  Balad  IZ  11  June 2011   June 2013  Director of Operations  AFOSI 11th Field Investigations Squadron  Joint Base San Antonio 12  June 2013   Present  Recruiting Flight Commander  AFROTC Detachment 880  Virginia Military Institute  Lexington  VA MAJOR AWARDS AND DECORATIONS Bronze Star Medal Meritorious Service Medal Joint Service Commendation Medal Air Force Commendation Medal with one silver leaf cluster Air Force Achievement Medal with two oak leaf clusters Army Achievement Medal PROFESSIONAL MEMBERSHIPS AND AFFILIATIONS Air Force Association Military Officers Association of America EFFECTIVE DATES OF PROMOTION  Airman Basic August 24  1993 Airman February 24  1994 Airman First Class December 24  1994 Senior Airman August 24  1996 Staff Sergeant July 1  1999 Technical Sergeant April 1  2004 Master Sergeant May 1  2008 Second Lieutenant August 6  2008 First Lieutenant August 6  2010 Captain August 6  2012  Current as of February 2015  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Captain Hubert Lesniak  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Give Close Menu ROTC Leadership Air Force ROTC Home Courses Info for Current Cadets Info for Prospective Cadets VMI AF Hall of Fame Faculty Capt  Mark A  Smith Recruiting Flight Commander  540 464 7587 AFROTC P   540  464 7354 F   540  464 7775 Virginia Military Institu